fields.description:
Create AgentControl handle for agent operations (codex pattern).

## Deliverables
- src/agent/control.ts

## Design (matching codex AgentControl)
```typescript
class AgentControl {
  // Weak ref to manager to avoid cycles
  private manager: WeakRef<AgentManagerState>;

  spawn(config, message, sessionSource?): Promise<AgentId>;
  send(id, message, interrupt?): Promise<string>;  // submission_id
  interrupt(id): Promise<void>;
  shutdown(id): Promise<void>;
  getStatus(id): Promise<Status>;
  subscribeStatus(id): Observable<Status>;
  list(): AgentInfo[];
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Weak reference pattern prevents memory cycles
- [ ] spawn() delegates to manager, returns agent_id
- [ ] send() queues message to agent, returns submission_id
- [ ] send() with interrupt=true interrupts current work first
- [ ] interrupt() stops agent's current turn
- [ ] shutdown() sends shutdown, removes from manager
- [ ] getStatus() returns current status (NotFound if missing)
- [ ] subscribeStatus() returns observable for status changes
- [ ] list() returns all agents with status
- [ ] Errors propagate correctly (AgentNotFound, ManagerDropped, etc.)
